Name: Autism
Description: Developmental disease that affects social interaction and communication

Name: Down syndrome
Description: Affects the physical growth delays,mild to moderate intellectual disability, and characteristic facial features.

Name: Hemophilia
Description: Causes prolonged bleading and easy bruising

Name: Color blindness
Description: Decreases  ability to see color or differences in color.

Name: Sickle cell disease
Description: Causes sickle cell shape blood vessels

Name: DiGeorge syndrome
Description: Causes  kidney problems, hearing loss and autoimmune disorders

Name: Canavan disease
Description: degenerative disorder that causes progressive damage to nerve cells in the brain

Name: Spinal muscular atrophy
Description: neuromuscular disorders that result in the loss of motor neurons and progressive muscle wasting
